n stellt somit einen wertvollen Beitrag dar, Krisen zukünftiger Projektfinanzierungsvorhaben zu vermeiden oder zu bewältigen  aWhile many financing projects go off without a hitch, many others are threatened by failure. The aim of this book is to describe the legal, economic, and sociological frameworks of project financing that must be taken into account as part of the risk management/crisis management process.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 0aCapital investments. 0aCorporationsxFinance. 0aProject management. 0aRisk management. 4aFlughafen. 4aGroßprojekt. 4aInsolvenz. 4aKrise. 4aProjektmanagement. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Finance / Financial Risk Management.2bisacsh1 aBöttcher, Jörg, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aWiebusch, Anja, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2016z9783110485103oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Economics 2016z9783110485158oZDB-23-DBV0 cEPUBz97831104475210 cprintz978311044745340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311044978540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110449785423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110449785.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DBVb2016  aZDB-23-DGGb2016